---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Document categories/sections
const manSections = [
  { id: "installation", title: "MECTOV(8) - Installation" },
  { id: "packages", title: "MECTOV-SYS(8) - Packages" },
  { id: "desktop", title: "MECTOV-DE(1) - Desktop Config" },
  { id: "performance", title: "MECTOV-OPT(8) - Performance" },
];
---

<Layout title="Documentation" description="Mectov Linux system manuals. Read instructions for installation, packages, desktop config, and kernel tuning.">
  <div class="container docs-container">
    
    <div class="docs-layout">
      
      <!-- Left Column: Man Page Index (Sidebar) -->
      <aside class="man-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-header">
          <span class="sidebar-title">MAN-INDEX</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-body">
          <p class="dir-title">/usr/share/man/</p>
          <ul class="man-toc">
            {manSections.map((sec, idx) => (
              <li>
                <button 
                  data-section-target={sec.id} 
                  class={`toc-btn ${idx === 0 ? 'active' : ''}`}
                >
                  <span class="tree-line">{idx === manSections.length - 1 ? '└── ' : '├── '}</span>
                  <span class="btn-text">{sec.title.split(' ')[0]}</span>
                </button>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- Right Column: Interactive Man Page Display -->
      <section class="man-display">
        
        <!-- SECTION: INSTALLATION -->
        <article id="man-installation" class="man-page active">
          <header class="man-header">
            <span>MECTOV(8)</span>
            <span class="man-header-center">Mectov System Administrator's Manual</span>
            <span>MECTOV(8)</span>
          </header>
          
          <div class="man-content">
            <h2>NAME</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">mectov - Arch Linux & CachyOS-based speed-optimized distribution installation guide</p>

            <h2>SYNOPSIS</h2>
            <p class="man-indent"><code>mectov-install [options] [target_device]</code></p>

            <h2>DESCRIPTION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              <strong>Mectov Linux</strong> is built specifically for users requiring extreme workstation responsiveness. It integrates the <strong>CachyOS repository</strong> and custom-compiled optimized kernel architectures (x86-64-v3 / x86-64-v4) directly into a stable Arch Linux baseline.
            </p>

            <h2>INSTALLATION PROCESS</h2>
            <h3 class="man-sub">1. Partitioning the Target Disk</h3>
            <p class="man-indent-2">
              For modern systems, GPT partition layout with UEFI boot is strictly recommended. Partition your target drive using <code>cfdisk</code> or <code>parted</code>:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block">
# Create UEFI Boot Partition (512M, EFI System type)
$ mkfs.fat -F 32 /dev/sdX1

# Create Root Partition (ext4, Btrfs, or XFS)
$ mkfs.btrfs -L MECTOV_ROOT /dev/sdX2
            </pre>

            <h3 class="man-sub">2. Bootstrapping the System</h3>
            <p class="man-indent-2">
              Mount your partitions and execute the bootstrap script to download optimized packages:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block">
$ mount /dev/sdX2 /mnt
$ mkdir -p /mnt/boot
$ mount /dev/sdX1 /mnt/boot

# Install basic packages and the optimized kernel
$ pacstrap -K /mnt base base-devel linux-cachyos linux-cachyos-headers linux-firmware neovim git
            </pre>

            <h2>BUGS</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">Report installation issues to the Mectov bugtracker at https://github.com/mectov-linux/mectov/issues</p>

            <h2>SEE ALSO</h2>
            <p class="man-indent"><code>pacman(8)</code>, <code>mkinitcpio(8)</code>, <code>cachyos-config(8)</code></p>
          </div>
          
          <footer class="man-footer">
            <span>Mectov 1.0</span>
            <span class="man-footer-center">2026-06-30</span>
            <span>MECTOV(8)</span>
          </footer>
        </article>

        <!-- SECTION: PACKAGES -->
        <article id="man-packages" class="man-page">
          <header class="man-header">
            <span>MECTOV-SYS(8)</span>
            <span class="man-header-center">Mectov System Administrator's Manual</span>
            <span>MECTOV-SYS(8)</span>
          </header>
          
          <div class="man-content">
            <h2>NAME</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">mectov-sys - Package repository config and maintenance</p>

            <h2>DESCRIPTION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              Mectov Linux utilizes a dual-tier package management ecosystem. It inherits all official <strong>Arch Linux</strong> repositories and prepends the <strong>CachyOS Repository</strong> database to retrieve optimized packages compiled with native optimizations.
            </p>

            <h2>REPOSITORIES</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              The package database order in <code>/etc/pacman.conf</code> is configured as follows:
            </p>
            <pre class="code-block">
[cachyos-v3]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/cachyos-mirrorlist

[cachyos-core-v3]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/cachyos-mirrorlist

[cachyos-extra-v3]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/cachyos-mirrorlist

[core]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist

[extra]
Include = /etc/pacman.d/mirrorlist
            </pre>

            <h2>BASIC OPERATIONS</h2>
            <h3 class="man-sub">Installing Packages</h3>
            <p class="man-indent-2">Install a package from the repositories using pacman:</p>
            <pre class="code-block">
$ sudo pacman -S alacritty
            </pre>

            <h3 class="man-sub">Sync and System Upgrade</h3>
            <p class="man-indent-2">Sync mirror lists and perform a complete system rolling-release upgrade:</p>
            <pre class="code-block">
$ sudo pacman -Syu
            </pre>
          </div>
          
          <footer class="man-footer">
            <span>Mectov 1.0</span>
            <span class="man-footer-center">2026-06-30</span>
            <span>MECTOV-SYS(8)</span>
          </footer>
        </article>

        <!-- SECTION: DESKTOP -->
        <article id="man-desktop" class="man-page">
          <header class="man-header">
            <span>MECTOV-DE(1)</span>
            <span class="man-header-center">Mectov User Commands Manual</span>
            <span>MECTOV-DE(1)</span>
          </header>
          
          <div class="man-content">
            <h2>NAME</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">mectov-de - Desktop interface configurations (KDE Plasma / Hyprland)</p>

            <h2>DESCRIPTION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              Mectov Linux ships with two preconfigured environments: a full-featured <strong>KDE Plasma 6 (Wayland)</strong> desktop for stability and a tiling-window compositor <strong>Hyprland</strong> for high-productivity development workflows.
            </p>

            <h2>HYPRLAND KEYBINDINGS</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">Standard keyboard configurations to control your desktop layout:</p>
            <pre class="code-block">
$mod = SUPER

# Core Windows controls
bind = $mod, Q, killactive,
bind = $mod, F, togglefloating,
bind = $mod, M, fullscreen,

# Launch applications
bind = $mod, RETURN, exec, alacritty
bind = $mod, D, exec, rofi -show drun

# Move focus with arrow keys
bind = $mod, left, movefocus, l
bind = $mod, right, movefocus, r
bind = $mod, up, movefocus, u
bind = $mod, down, movefocus, d
            </pre>

            <h2>DOTFILES LOCATION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">All desktop customization files reside in the user directory:</p>
            <p class="man-indent-2"><code>~/.config/hypr/</code> - Window manager configuration</p>
            <p class="man-indent-2"><code>~/.config/alacritty/</code> - Terminal style files</p>
            <p class="man-indent-2"><code>~/.config/waybar/</code> - Status bar config & layouts</p>
          </div>
          
          <footer class="man-footer">
            <span>Mectov 1.0</span>
            <span class="man-footer-center">2026-06-30</span>
            <span>MECTOV-DE(1)</span>
          </footer>
        </article>

        <!-- SECTION: PERFORMANCE -->
        <article id="man-performance" class="man-page">
          <header class="man-header">
            <span>MECTOV-OPT(8)</span>
            <span class="man-header-center">Mectov System Administrator's Manual</span>
            <span>MECTOV-OPT(8)</span>
          </header>
          
          <div class="man-content">
            <h2>NAME</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">mectov-opt - Performance tuning and kernel scheduling optimizations</p>

            <h2>DESCRIPTION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              The core strength of Mectov Linux is its speed. Hardware scheduling, memory cache parameters, and network packet handlers are fine-tuned for high throughput.
            </p>

            <h2>KERNEL SCHEDULER: BORE</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">
              By default, Mectov runs the **BORE (Burst-Oriented Response Enhancer)** scheduler. It optimizes scheduling priorities dynamically, preventing background tasks from bottlenecking your foreground desktop UI.
            </p>

            <h2>CPU & THERMAL CONFIGURATION</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">Ensure optimal CPU governors and thermal configurations are active:</p>
            <pre class="code-block">
# Check active CPU governor (performance/schedutil)
$ cat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor

# Enable performance governor on AC power
$ sudo cpupower frequency-set -g performance
            </pre>

            <h2>SYSCTL KERNEL PARAMETERS</h2>
            <p class="man-indent">Recommended tweaks configured in <code>/etc/sysctl.d/99-mectov.conf</code>:</p>
            <pre class="code-block">
# Decrease virtual memory swap aggressive level
vm.swappiness = 10

# Increase maximum file descriptors limits
fs.file-max = 2097152

# Speed up TCP window scaling
net.core.rmem_max = 16777216
net.core.wmem_max = 16777216
            </pre>
          </div>
          
          <footer class="man-footer">
            <span>Mectov 1.0</span>
            <span class="man-footer-center">2026-06-30</span>
            <span>MECTOV-OPT(8)</span>
          </footer>
        </article>

      </section>
      
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.docs-container {
  padding-top: 3rem;
}

.docs-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
  align-items: start;
}

@media (max-width: 850px) {
  .docs-layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}

/* Sidebar Index Styles */
.man-sidebar {
  background-color: #000;
  border: 3px solid var(--text-primary);
  box-shadow: 5px 5px 0 var(--accent-red);
}

.sidebar-header {
  background-color: var(--text-primary);
  color: var(--bg-color);
  padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
}

.sidebar-body {
  padding: 1rem;
}

.dir-title {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  color: var(--text-muted);
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.man-toc {
  list-style: none;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
}

.man-toc li {
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

.toc-btn {
  background: none;
  border: none;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  text-align: left;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: 0.2rem 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  width: 100%;
  transition: none;
}

.toc-btn:hover .btn-text {
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
  background-color: rgba(0, 255, 209, 0.1);
}

.toc-btn.active .btn-text {
  color: var(--bg-color);
  background-color: var(--accent-cyan);
  font-weight: bold;
}

.tree-line {
  color: var(--text-muted);
  white-space: pre;
}

.btn-text {
  padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
}

/* Man Display Styles */
.man-display {
  background-color: #000;
  border: 3px solid var(--accent-cyan);
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--text-primary);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.man-page {
  display: none;
  padding: 1.5rem;
}

.man-page.active {
  display: block;
}

.man-header, .man-footer {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent-cyan);
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
}

.man-footer {
  border-bottom: none;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--accent-cyan);
  padding-bottom: 0;
  padding-top: 0.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0;
  margin-top: 2rem;
}

.man-header-center, .man-footer-center {
  text-align: center;
}

/* Man contents typography */
.man-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #FFF;
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px dashed rgba(0, 255, 209, 0.3);
  padding-bottom: 0.2rem;
}

.man-content h2:first-of-type {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.man-content p {
  color: var(--text-primary);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}

.man-indent {
  padding-left: 2rem;
}

.man-indent-2 {
  padding-left: 3rem;
}

.man-sub {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--accent-red);
  margin-top: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  padding-left: 2rem;
}

.man-content code {
  background-color: #101018;
  color: var(--accent-cyan);
  padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 209, 0.2);
}

.code-block {
  background-color: #050508;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 209, 0.3);
  padding: 1rem;
  margin: 1rem 0 1rem 2rem;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  word-wrap: break-word;
}
</style>

<script>
  // Simple tab switching logic for Man Pages
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.toc-btn');
    const pages = document.querySelectorAll('.man-page');

    buttons.forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const targetId = button.getAttribute('data-section-target');
        
        // Remove active class from all buttons and pages
        buttons.forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
        pages.forEach(pg => pg.classList.remove('active'));

        // Add active class to clicked button and target page
        button.classList.add('active');
        const targetPage = document.getElementById(`man-${targetId}`);
        if (targetPage) {
          targetPage.classList.add('active');
          // Scroll page view back to top if offscreen
          window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'auto' });
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>
